notes: "Tier-3 fault_lines vertical descent. Player enters at the top of a ~16000-micro_unit shaft and descends through six platforms — three wider shelves (entry, mid-shaft one_way, exit) interleaved with three narrow ledges that alternate sides across the shaft. Two checkpoints (on the left narrow ledge at y=10700 and the lower right narrow ledge at y=4700) break the descent into three sections of roughly equal vertical span. Four ember pickups totaling 8 ember (1+2+2+3) give the player ~2 dashes or one sustained glide per section, with a larger payout near the exit. A wide lava bed occupies the bottom of the shaft to the left of the exit shelf; the absolute floor is void, so falling past the exit shelf (whether short or long) is lethal. Side-wall spike strips mid-shaft punish lateral overshoot during dashes — the fault_lines region signature. Tier 3 balance band: 5-15 deaths acceptable per median_deaths_per_level; first-clear target ~3.3 minutes for a skilled player, within the tier-3 [120000, 300000] tolerance band."
